item.dc:creator: @Redemtion Redemtion
item.description:
@Redemtion wrote:

Another thing is if you have all the commands in commands.java that have a certain username requirement to do the command, just do setrights [yourname] 2
0 = normal
1 = Mod
2 = Admin

item.title: Rscalifornia, need help!
item.dc:creator: @Redemtion Redemtion
item.description:
@Redemtion wrote:

Ambition Rsps:

if your using the matrix based source, search you character name, sometimes it ends up in the server.java and that is where you see some player rights, and you could add your name to the player rights in the server.java, but thats the easy way out, other then that just search for a file converter and change the .p into a .java

Why install a file converter when you can just do it all in cmd? just type cd (path(will change the directory from C:/Users/System32)) then rn (the original file) (new file WITH extension) also theres nothing in server.java about player rights. I’m using the same base that OP is using, so just follow my way xD
so cmd example of Directory change
cd C:/Users/ME/Desktop
Then renaming…
rn something.p something.txt
